Mission Oflameron

To train compact AI models for writing the script for the "Mission Oflameron" project, we will develop a dataset with examples based on the already written material https://github.com/vallshmeleff/ai-prompts-for-screenplay-plan

Prompt to AI

“Is it possible to train compact AI models like Qwen2.5 (7B) to write fragments of the MissionOflameron script?”

AI response

Yes, it is absolutely possible and is a great solution for such a creative challenge. Models of size 7B are perfectly amenable to additional training (Fine-Tuning) for a specific style, lore and script format on ordinary consumer or available cloud equipment.

Advantages of Qwen 2.5 (7B) for this task

Strong foundation: Qwen 2.5 has an excellent understanding of context and logic.
Multilingual: The model works perfectly with Russian and English languages.
Long Context: Supports large amounts of text, which is important for scripting.

How to implement fine-tuning

Dataset preparation. This is the most important step for maintaining the uniqueness of "MissionOflameron."
Collect all existing texts, design documents (design docs), character descriptions, and lore.
Break the material into Request -> Response pairs (e.g., Scene Input -> Script Text).
Use script formatting (e.g., Fountain or a standard script format) to help the model learn the structure.
Training method (LoRA / QLoRA). Training the entire model (Full Fine-Tuning) is too expensive. Use PEFT (Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning), specifically the QLoRA method.
It freezes the main model and trains only a small percentage of adapters.
Allows training on a single GPU (e.g., RTX 3090, RTX 4090, or cloud A10G / T4).
Tools to Get You Started
You don't need to write code from scratch. Use ready-made tools:
Unsloth: Maximizes training speed for Qwen series models and reduces video memory consumption.
LLaMA-Factory: A convenient tool with a web interface for customizing the training process without extensive programming.
Hugging Face TRL: A library for custom Python scripts.

Alternative: RAG and Few-Shot Prompting
Before retraining, try giving the model context directly.
Place the "MissionOflameron" lore in the system prompt or vector database (RAG).
Show the model 2-3 examples of ideal scene writing (Few-Shot).
For 7B models, this is often enough to capture the desired tone without the need for training.

